                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="18239" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 27 Jun 2006 06:03:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Costin, can you please have a look at this and see what we can do about it? We might end up having to ship the persistence DTD in our own jar file if the providers don&apos;t include it in a well-defined location... or dispense with our DTD validation in PersistenceUnitReader.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18315" author="costin" created="Thu, 29 Jun 2006 04:36:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added some lookup strategies (which work on hibernate). If no XSD is found then the reader will still do validation (which is required) but will fallback to the xml parser so the schema location specified inside the XML will be used (by default, this points to java.sun.com site so it will require network access).&lt;br/&gt;
We might add a flag to turn on validation on and off for corner cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
